message.content:
Before Cam broke his right arm, he was able to type 9 words per minute on his phone which equates to 9 * 5 = 45 words in 5 minutes.
After he broke his arm, he had to use his left hand and could only type 6 words per minute which equates to 6 * 5 = 30 words in 5 minutes.
The difference between the number of words he could type in 5 minutes before and after he broke his arm is 45 - 30 = 15 words.
